        <!-- Q1 -->
        <details class="group/faq border-b border-hairline cursor-pointer" open>
          <summary
            class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-base font-semibold text-primary font-display list-none"
          >
            Is my data safe? Do you store any inputs?
            <span
              class="text-slate group-open/faq:rotate-180 transition-transform"
              >&darr;</span
            >
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-slate leading-relaxed">
            Yes, your data is 100% safe. BoardTools is built as a fully static
            website. All operations, conversions, computations, and image
            rendering happen entirely inside your local browser. No data, files,
            or strings are ever transmitted to any external servers.
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- Q2 -->
        <details class="group/faq border-b border-hairline cursor-pointer">
          <summary
            class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-base font-semibold text-primary font-display list-none"
          >
            How does the canvas whiteboard save its state?
            <span
              class="text-slate group-open/faq:rotate-180 transition-transform"
              >&darr;</span
            >
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-slate leading-relaxed">
            The whiteboard saves its sketches and sticky notes content directly
            to your local browser storage (`localStorage`). If you refresh or
            close the tab, your draft will be preserved. You can also click the
            "Export PNG" button to download a static snapshot to your computer.
